#
# CP2K AIMD Grotthuss — Well-Tempered Metadynamics (s121, 2026-04-23)
# Goal: compute free energy profile для excess proton transfer between
# (a) Fe-chemisorbed state и (b) bulk water state. Get barrier + equilibrium constant.
#
# Answers definitively:
#   - Is Fe-chemi thermodynamic minimum or kinetic trap?
#   - What's the barrier for desorption Fe-H → H in water?
#   - What's the equilibrium ratio Fe-chemi / bulk-water at 300K?
#
# System: 3x3x1 mackinawite + 12 H2O + 1 H+ = 73 atoms (same as 3×3×1 production)
# Method: PBE-D3(BJ), nspin=1, NVT 300K, dt=0.5 fs
# Metadynamics: Well-Tempered, CV = proton-Fe coordination number
#
# CV design (COORDINATION):
#   n_FeH = Σ_k [1 - (d_Fe_k - H_excess / R0)^NN] / [1 - (d_Fe_k - H_excess / R0)^NN+MM]
#   where H_excess is defined via EXCLUDE_HYDROGENS_OF... but simpler:
#   Use DISTANCE_POINT_PLANE between excess H atom and Fe slab centroid plane
#   Or: PROTON_COORD with switching on d_O(H) to detect "excess" H dynamically
#
# Chosen: COORDINATION NUMBER with ATOMS=[all_Fe], POINTS=[excess_H_tracer].
# Problem: "excess H" atom identity changes during Grotthuss → need fictitious atom
#           OR average CV over all H (simpler).
# Chosen v1 (simplest): track specific atom index 37 (current excess H in 3×3×1
#           from fe_h_distance analysis, 100% Fe-chemisorbed).
#           Start METADYN from existing equilibrated structure where H_37 is on Fe.
#           Bias CV = coordination number of H_37 with all 18 Fe atoms.
#           Expected: initial CV ≈ 1 (Fe-chemi), driven toward CV < 0.1 (water).
#
# Well-Tempered params (s121 review: APPROVE with caveats from Physicist, BLOCKED by Chemist
# on identity-CV concern. Compromise: accepted identity CV for 3×3×1 test where s121
# showed H_37 is stuck on Fe — minimal Grotthuss interference expected. FES interpretation
# is "forward desorption barrier of H_37 from Fe surface", not general excess-proton FES.
# Caveat documented in SI. Reverse rate + full FES requires better CV — deferred):
#   Gaussian height: 1.0 kJ/mol (~0.4 kT)
#   Gaussian width σ: 0.05 (CV units, dimensionless coordination number)
#   Deposit every: 100 steps (50 fs)
#   WT factor γ: 10 → ΔT = (γ-1)T = 2700 K (fixed from s121 review)
#   Total steps: 100000 (50 ps) — s121 Physicist: +40% for safety margin on convergence
#   + WALL potential on CV > 1.2 to prevent unphysical over-coordination (s121 Physicist)
#
# REVIEW s121 APPROVED (Physicist) with these fixes applied.
# Chemist concern: CV tracks atom H_37, not excess charge. For 3×3×1 H_37 chronically
# Fe-chemisorbed per fe_h_distance — valid. For 3×3×2 or different systems a
# weighted-sum CV would be needed. Will document in SI-E.
#

&GLOBAL
  PROJECT grotthuss_metadyn
  RUN_TYPE MD
  PRINT_LEVEL LOW
  WALLTIME -1
  PREFERRED_DIAG_LIBRARY SCALAPACK
&END GLOBAL

&FORCE_EVAL
  METHOD Quickstep
  &DFT
    BASIS_SET_FILE_NAME BASIS_MOLOPT
    POTENTIAL_FILE_NAME GTH_POTENTIALS
    CHARGE 1

    &QS
      EPS_DEFAULT 1.0E-12
      EXTRAPOLATION ASPC
      EXTRAPOLATION_ORDER 3
    &END QS

    &MGRID
      CUTOFF 320
      REL_CUTOFF 40
      NGRIDS 4
    &END MGRID

    &XC
      &XC_FUNCTIONAL PBE
      &END XC_FUNCTIONAL
      &VDW_POTENTIAL
        POTENTIAL_TYPE PAIR_POTENTIAL
        &PAIR_POTENTIAL
          TYPE DFTD3(BJ)
          REFERENCE_FUNCTIONAL PBE
        &END PAIR_POTENTIAL
      &END VDW_POTENTIAL
    &END XC

    &SCF
      SCF_GUESS RESTART
      MAX_SCF 300
      EPS_SCF 1.0E-5
      ADDED_MOS 40
      &DIAGONALIZATION
        ALGORITHM STANDARD
      &END DIAGONALIZATION
      &MIXING
        METHOD BROYDEN_MIXING
        ALPHA 0.2
        NBROYDEN 8
      &END MIXING
      &SMEAR
        METHOD FERMI_DIRAC
        ELECTRONIC_TEMPERATURE [K] 500
      &END SMEAR
      &OUTER_SCF
        EPS_SCF 1.0E-5
        MAX_SCF 10
      &END OUTER_SCF
    &END SCF
  &END DFT

  &SUBSYS
    &CELL
      A  11.022  0.000  0.000
      B   0.000 11.022  0.000
      C   0.000  0.000  6.500
      PERIODIC XYZ
    &END CELL

    &TOPOLOGY
      COORD_FILE_NAME structure.xyz
      COORD_FILE_FORMAT XYZ
    &END TOPOLOGY

    &COLVAR
      &COORDINATION
        ! Coordination number of excess H_37 (1-based atom #38)
        ! with all 18 Fe atoms (1-based indices from structure.xyz):
        ! Fe: [1, 2, 5, 6, 9, 10, 13, 14, 17, 18, 21, 22, 25, 26, 29, 30, 33, 34]
        ATOMS_FROM 38
        ATOMS_TO   1 2 5 6 9 10 13 14 17 18 21 22 25 26 29 30 33 34
        R_0 [angstrom] 2.0                ! switching radius (midway Fe-H 1.6 and bulk 2.5)
        NN 6
        ND 12
      &END COORDINATION
    &END COLVAR

    &KIND Fe
      BASIS_SET DZVP-MOLOPT-SR-GTH
      POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q16
    &END KIND
    &KIND S
      BASIS_SET DZVP-MOLOPT-SR-GTH
      POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q6
    &END KIND
    &KIND O
      BASIS_SET DZVP-MOLOPT-SR-GTH
      POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q6
    &END KIND
    &KIND H
      BASIS_SET DZVP-MOLOPT-SR-GTH
      POTENTIAL GTH-PBE-q1
    &END KIND
  &END SUBSYS
&END FORCE_EVAL

&MOTION
  &MD
    ENSEMBLE NVT
    STEPS 100000                         ! 50 ps (s121 review: safety for WT convergence)
    TIMESTEP [fs] 0.5
    TEMPERATURE [K] 300.0
    &THERMOSTAT
      TYPE NOSE
      REGION GLOBAL
      &NOSE
        LENGTH 3
        TIMECON [fs] 500.0
        MTS 2
      &END NOSE
    &END THERMOSTAT
  &END MD

  &FREE_ENERGY
    METHOD METADYN
    &METADYN
      DO_HILLS .TRUE.
      USE_PLUMED .FALSE.                 ! native CP2K metadyn
      WW [kjmol] 1.0                     ! Gaussian height (0.4 kT)
      NT_HILLS 100                       ! deposit every 100 MD steps = 50 fs
      WELL_TEMPERED .TRUE.
      WTGAMMA 10                         ! bias factor; ΔT = (γ-1)T = 2700 K
      ! NOTE: TEMPERATURE keyword в &METADYN = для Lagrangian scheme ТОЛЬКО.
      ! Для WT-MetaD физическая T берётся из thermostat. DELTA_T альтернатива WTGAMMA.
      &METAVAR
        COLVAR 1                         ! points to COLVAR above
        SCALE 0.05                       ! Gaussian width σ in CV units
        ! Wall potentials to prevent unphysical CV excursions (s121 Physicist)
        &WALL
          TYPE QUARTIC
          POSITION 1.2                   ! upper bound (typical chemisorbed ≈1)
          &QUARTIC
            DIRECTION WALL_PLUS
            K [kjmol] 500.0
          &END QUARTIC
        &END WALL
        &WALL
          TYPE QUARTIC
          POSITION -0.1                  ! lower bound (soft, CV geometrically ≥0)
          &QUARTIC
            DIRECTION WALL_MINUS
            K [kjmol] 500.0
          &END QUARTIC
        &END WALL
      &END METAVAR
      &PRINT
        &HILLS
          &EACH
            MD 100
          &END EACH
        &END HILLS
        &COLVAR
          &EACH
            MD 10
          &END EACH
        &END COLVAR
      &END PRINT
    &END METADYN
  &END FREE_ENERGY

  &PRINT
    &TRAJECTORY
      &EACH
        MD 1
      &END EACH
      FORMAT XYZ
    &END TRAJECTORY
    &VELOCITIES
      &EACH
        MD 10
      &END EACH
    &END VELOCITIES
    &RESTART
      &EACH
        MD 10
      &END EACH
      BACKUP_COPIES 2
    &END RESTART
    &RESTART_HISTORY
      &EACH
        MD 2000
      &END EACH
    &END RESTART_HISTORY
  &END PRINT
&END MOTION
